A Minimal Book Example John Doe 2022-10-08 Chapter 1 Project Euler Project Euler has a series of challenging coding problems. The first set of problems are over 20 years old - we’re allowed to discuss solutions to these out in the open. They respectfully ask that we don’t discuss solutions of more recent puzzles. I’ve put this book together to show how some of these puzzles can be solved with R + tidyverse-style packages + other packages as useful, as well as offering somewhere for R useRs to get some sensible Pull Requests in for #Hacktoberfest.
